  "body": "```\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.7.3-stable\r\nGit Commit: 4bb3c89d44e372e6a9ab85a8be0c9345265c763a\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [63 62]\r\nNetwork Id: 1\r\nGo Version: go1.9.2\r\nOperating System: linux\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/usr/local/go\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe have an address with a balance of 0.02138 ETH\r\n```\r\n> addr='0x....';\r\n> eth.getBalance(addr);\r\n21380000000000000\r\n```\r\nUsing gasPrice = 30 Gwei, gas = 21000, we expect 0.00063 ETH in transaction fee, so we try to send 0.02075 ETH.\r\n\r\n```\r\n    [gasPrice] => 0x6fc23ac00\r\n    [gas] => 0x5208\r\n    [value] => 0x49b803db16e000\r\n    [to] => 0x..\r\n    [from] => 0x..\r\n\r\n```\r\nFailing with 'insufficient funds for gas * price + value'. Why?",
